snippet.textDisplay:
This anime is so accurate. Look out for stuff like physical traits like flagella and color to give hints of the actual type of bacteria they are fighting.

Some stuff may me more metaphorical than and actual representation of the mechanics, but the parallels are there.

I think platelets are made by breaking off pieces of a larger cell? That's why they are smaller. Also, because teaching children to be careful when crossing streets and making excursions, they used that as a metaphor, as the platelets plug on hazard zones.

In some cases, the emotional reactions are more related to the patients's reaction, but the characters are doing it.

By all means watch and review it all, there aren't any wasted episodes.

But my favorites are scrape wound, food poisoning, cedar pollen allergy, the cancer 2- episode arc, and hemorragic shock, the 2-part season finale.
